  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and multi-layered, involving international, national, and institutional regulations:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee Guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the US)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n- Specific criminal statutes defining money laundering offenses\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement comprehensive AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Internal control mechanisms\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment for offenders\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Extradition agreements\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
